TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xasDX6n0WOhQ005S56y2r
SUMMARY:Johnny &amp\; Reg @ Perihelion Brewery
DTSTAMP:20260413T010440Z
DTSTART:20260722T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Johnny & Reg grew from late-night jam sessions and a shared lov
	e of funky\, soulful music. Their sound drifts through blue notes and groo
	ves\, equal parts raw and refined. It carries the dust of back roads and t
	he glow of late-night campfires — acoustic wanderers moving from town to t
	own with a suitcase of blues\, jazz-tinged melodies\, and stories gathered
	 along the way. The sound leans into raw wood and warm strings\, equal par
	ts grit and grace\, always shaped by the places they pass through. Eclecti
	c\, earthy\, and effortlessly heartfelt.With tight harmonies\, weathered r
	hythms\, and a laid-back charm\, they will bring a rich\, rootsy energy to
	 Perihelion’s outdoor Patio!\n\nhttps://www.perihelion.beer/events/2026/7/
	21/johnny-amp-red-perihelion-brewery
URL:https://www.perihelion.beer/events/2026/7/21/johnny-amp-red-perihelion-
	brewery
LOCATION:Perihelion Brewery\, 2800 16th Ave South\, Seattle\, WA 98144
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pSGrv9Ps_tRTKVHq4FY9N
SUMMARY:Bryan John Appleby @ Perihelion Brewery
DTSTAMP:20260413T010440Z
DTSTART:20260729T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Bryan John Appleby is a singer/songwriter and multi-instrumenta
	list based in Seattle. His folk-centric body of work draws elements from m
	id-century pop\, wall-of-sound\, psychodelia\, tropicália\, and classic ci
	nema.  Appleby’s most recent effort\, Underwater Easy Breathing (Plume Rec
	ords) exemplifies a distinct production palette and fantastical tendencies
	. Lush\, coastal\, synth-laced\; the album is a natural next step in his w
	andering\, often densely layered folk repertoire.Join us on the patio to e
	njoy this wonderful performace!\n\nhttps://www.perihelion.beer/events/2026
	/4/12/bryan-john-appleby-perihelion-brewery
URL:https://www.perihelion.beer/events/2026/4/12/bryan-john-appleby-perihel
	ion-brewery
LOCATION:Perihelion Brewery\, 2800 16th Ave South\, Seattle\, WA 98144
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
